text: It was so sweet
And so mean
Does anyone else listen to Commander Cookout?
In today's episode they propose that aggro, combo, control and voltron are the 4 super archetypes in EDH, and everything else is a subset of combination of those.

what distinguishes voltron from aggro?
not saying I disagree, I'm just curious what prevents one of those from being a subset of the other
Good question. I'm not there yet
i think voltron is particularly around the commander killing with commander damage, while aggro is killing with combat damage in general?
thats how i differentiate
That is one distinct difference, true
Voltron I always assuming is a buffed creature, either via equipment, auras or maybe exalted. Aggro I think of people losing games.
Group hug (true hug that doesn't care about winning) is probably its own archetype, too
I've never run into one of those
Kynaios and Tiro has instantly become one of my favorite decks, but I'm still out to win after I give people stuff :smile:
Are you playing combo?
Nah, it's just fun. For being a blackless commander, they play like a black mage would---political, pragmatic, exchanging favors that will ultimately end up in their favor...
That's just how I like playing it, at least
Sounds fun. I like playing politics and instituting policies that are ultimately bad for my opponents.
Voltron is combo aggro isn't it?
What is combo?
Personally, I feel that all styles of magic are really just one: combo
Combo is winning by some means other than combat damage (usually)
Even control usually wins by combo or aggro
combo is about a combinaiton of cards that loop a significant amount of times
Attacking with Goblin Guide 10 times is a combo you guise
burn i wouldn’t call combo
No
lands + spells is a pretty good combo
Burn is a combo deck where any 7 spells win
That's more spellslinger, maybe
Burn, also, had traditionally been unviable in EDH. Though, more and more, I think it's becoming playable
In other formats the archetype centers around cheap, efficient damage spells
maybe this is what is cool about edh, is that things don’t fit cleanly into archetypes. i think my mono black deck wins with combos, but really its a control deck
probably not worth my time to figure out what to call things
EDH is art

I kinda like the Commander Cookout guys... they are fun and their podcast has great audio. Easy on my headphones while I'm at work.  :slightly_smiling_face: 
I listened to the Surrak episode... I'll check this archetype one out...
Yeah, and they have a wicked theme song
Like three seconds in I'm like "these dudes are Canadian, right?"
Really good audio
Super duper
Just heard the phrase "I was beating wholesale ass" in a canadian accent which I'm tempted to make a ringtone. Thanks for the podcast recommendation!
You're welcome!
If you make that a ring tone, please share
Jeeze Dean, if only you worked this hard selling our podcast
Heh, well...yeah, I got nothing.
I feel like I should do a whole episode or maybe just a segment where I use my teacher voice trying to teach a lesson to naughty kids
Lol, do a recurring etiquette segment.
you guys did pretty good on your podcast... I listened to episode 1 on YouTube (and subscribed). It was a great listen, well done!
Thanks! Episode 2 is out now, and episode 3 is out tomorrow
kool... I'll cue them up!
I don't know about the Cookout folks - pretty judgy about other folk's decks without presenting any credentials about their own expertise.
The cookout guys make the same mistake of assuming the EDHREC page is a decklist and then proceed to complain about the results.
Eh. They use it like Don uses it.
They try to avoid popular cards.
No - they keep calling it a "decklist" and how bland it is.
It isn't a decklist
Huh. What episode are you listening to?
0 - Zada.
Hm.
Also bland vs. Spice is just their cookout gimmick
They said Don posted a "decklist" to Reddit or somewhere and kept calling it "milk".
Oh I get the shtick, but actually compare a real list vs a list of individual card recommendations based on basically popularity.
Listening to all these new podcasts makes me wanna start my own...
It's the implicit disparaging of EDHREC as a netdecker's hangout I dislike.
You're a loyal company man, Henry. I like that.
That's only part of it, really. EDHREC is a just a resource vs a decklist generator, so I dislike anyone who disparages the tool because it doesn't auto-generate their deck.
I will hafta listen to episode 0... i liked the Surrak episode, but havent listen to anything else. I definitely dont like negativity tho, so sure my opinion will change after listening to 0.
Talk to JC about auto generated decks from EDHREC.
Because JC and I need more topics to argue about?
I still really enjoy the CC. I didn't really perceive any negativity.
I'm only on the first episode so it may change.
Oh, it's not an argument, but he's used EDHREC to auto generate decks before, I believe.
(you and he get along, right? Apart from your fundamentally contrarian nature :wink:)
Oh we do, we just come at Magic from fundamentally different viewpoints.
Sure. That makes sense.
I've used the average decklist too, but just to see if I like the commander doing the typical thing
